BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF OHIO:
Section 1. (A) The Director of Children and Youth shall 7
establish and administer, with the assistance of the Director of 8
Natural Resources, a one-time grant program that provides up to 9
seventy-five per cent reimbursement to local government entities 10
for the acquisition, development, or rehabilitation of outdoor 11
spaces, parks, playgrounds, pools, splash pads, and recreation 12
centers. 13
(B) A local government entity, including a township, 14
village, city, county, park district, joint recreation district, 15
and conservancy district may apply to the Director of Children 16
and Youth for a grant under this section. The applicant shall 17
include the following in the application: 18
(1) Proof that the applicant holds the title to or has a 19

